== Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the saucepan. Cover with a lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Beef Chilli ==

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) using a #garlic press{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic and @Central American style spice mix{1%tsp} into the beef. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%secs}.

> Add less spice mix if you'd prefer things milder.

Pour the @tomato passata{240%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @water for the sauce{150%ml} into the frying pan. Add a @?sugar{pinch} (if you have any). Stir together and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

== Tomato Salsa ==

Meanwhile, quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Pop them into a #small bowl{} with the @olive oil for the salsa{1%tsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together, then set your salsa aside.

== Assembly ==

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the beef chilli, tomato salsa and grated Cheddar in separate sections over the rice, then add a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}.

Finish with a sprinkle of @chilli flakes{1%tsp} for those who'd like some more heat (careful, they're hot)!

Enjoy!